        {
            "heading": "Kubernetes",
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "{% embed url=\"https://trustedsec.com/blog/kubernetes-for-pentesters-part-1\" %}\n{% embed url=\"https://blog.appsecco.com/a-pentesters-approach-to-kubernetes-security-part-1-2b328252954a\" %}\n{% embed url=\"https://blog.appsecco.com/a-pentesters-approach-to-kubernetes-security-part-2-8efac412fbc5\" %}\n{% embed url=\"https://bobvanderstaak.medium.com/penetration-testing-a-kubernetes-environment-72719f9e1010\" %}"
        },
        {
            "heading": "Concepts",
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "Kubernetes is a security orchestrator\n Kubernetes master provides an API to interact with nodes\n Each Kubernetes node run kubelet to interact with API and kube-proxy to refect Kubernetes networking services on each node.\n Kubernetes objects are abstractions of states of your system.\n Pods: collection of container share a network and namespace in the same node.\n Services: Group of pods running in the cluster.\n Volumes: directory accesible to all containers in a pod. Solves the problem of loose info when container crash and restart.\n Namespaces: scope of Kubernetes objects, like a workspace (dev-space)."
        },
        {
            "heading": "Commands",
            "type": "code_block",
            "content": [
                "# kubectl cli for run commands against Kubernetes clusters",
                "# Get info",
                "kubectl cluster-info",
                "# Get other objects info",
                "kubectl get nodes",
                "kubectl get pods",
                "kubectl get services",
                "# Deploy",
                "kubectl run nginxdeployment --image=nginx:alpine",
                "# Port forward to local machine",
                "kubectl port-forward <PODNAME> 1234:80",
                "# Deleting things",
                "kubectl delete pod",
                "# Shell in pod",
                "kubectl exec -it <PODNAME> sh",
                "# Check pod log",
                "kubectl logs <PODNAME>",
                "# List API resources",
                "kubectl api-resources",
                "# Check permissions",
                "kubectl auth can-i create pods",
                "# Get secrets",
                "kubectl get secrets <SECRETNAME> -o yaml",
                "# Get more info of specific pod",
                "kubectl describe pod <PODNAME>",
                "# Get cluster info",
                "kubectl cluster-info dump",
                "",
                "# Known vulns",
                "CVE-2016-9962",
                "CVE-2018-1002105",
                "CVE-2019-5736",
                "CVE-2019-9901"
            ]
        },
